                    </button>
                    <button class="btn buy-now">
                        <i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> Buy Now
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Description Section -->
        <div class="description-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Product Description</h2>
            <p class="description">
                Experience the timeless elegance of our Banarasi Silk Saree, meticulously handwoven by master artisans in Varanasi. This exquisite piece features intricate brocade patterns inspired by Mughal architecture, woven with pure gold and silver zari threads. The rich maroon base is adorned with floral motifs and traditional paisley designs, creating a luxurious drape that embodies centuries of weaving heritage. 
                
                Each saree takes approximately 15-20 days to complete, with the intricate patterns requiring exceptional skill and precision. The border features a classic design inspired by temple architecture, while the pallu showcases elaborate floral motifs that shimmer as they catch the light. Made with the finest Banarasi silk, this saree has a distinctive weight and luster that ensures it drapes beautifully and lasts for generations.
                
                This saree is perfect for weddings, festive occasions, and cultural celebrations. It comes with a matching blouse piece and is packaged in a handcrafted wooden box with traditional Indian motifs.
            </p>
            
            <!-- Artist Story -->
            <div class="artist-story">
                <div class="artist-image-placeholder">
                    <i class="fas fa-user-circle" style="font-size: 150px; color: #ddd;"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="artist-details">
                    <h3 class="artist-name">Meera Devi</h3>
                    <p>Meera Devi comes from a family of weavers in Varanasi with six generations of expertise in Banarasi silk weaving. She learned the craft from her grandmother and has been creating exquisite sarees for over 25 years. Meera specializes in traditional designs and has won several national awards for preserving this ancient art form. Each of her creations tells a story of heritage, patience, and extraordinary craftsmanship.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Reviews Section -->
        <div class="reviews-section">
            <h2 class="section-title">Customer Reviews</h2>
            
            <div class="review">
                <div class="reviewer-details">
                    <div class="reviewer">Priya Sharma</div>
                    <div class="review-date">October 12, 2023</div>
                    <div class="stars">
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="review-content">
                    <p>Absolutely breathtaking! The zari work is exquisite and the silk quality is exceptional. Received so many compliments at my brother's wedding. The packaging was also very elegant. Will definitely purchase from RangRiti again!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="review">
                <div class="reviewer-details">
                    <div class="reviewer">Rajiv Mehta</div>
                    <div class="review-date">September 28, 2023</div>
                    <div class="stars">
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
                        <i class="fas fa-star"></i>
